klogger - C++ Thread-Safe logger lib
========================================

Overview:
---------
klogger is a simple, thread-safe singleton logger library for C++17.
It supports logging to both stderr and a log file, multiple log levels,
exception logging, and unknown exception handling. Designed for easy
integration into any C++ project using CMake.

Basic Usage:
------------
Include the logger header:

    #include <klogger/logger.h>

Initialize the logger (optional but recommended):

    klogger::Logger::instance().init("app.log");

Log messages using macros:

    LOG_DEBUG("Debug message");
    LOG_INFO("Info message");
    LOG_WARN("Warning message");
    LOG_ERROR("Error message");
    LOG_FATAL("Fatal error message");

Log exceptions:

    try {
        throw std::runtime_error("Failure");
    } catch (const std::exception& e) {
        LOG_EXCEPTION(e);
    }

Handle unknown exceptions:

    try {
        throw 42;
    } catch (...) {
        LOG_UNKNOWN_EXCEPTION();
    }

Shutdown the logger (optional):

    klogger::Logger::instance().shutdown();

Log Output Format:
------------------
Each log entry is formatted as:

    YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS.mmm [LEVEL] [file:line] message

Example:

    2026-01-16 21:18:42.123 [INFO] [main.cpp:14] Application started

CMake Integration:
------------------
There are two ways to integrate klogger into your project.

1. Using `add_subdirectory`:

   Project structure:

       my_project/
       ├── CMakeLists.txt
       ├── src/main.cpp
       └── external/klogger  (cloned or submodule)

   Example CMakeLists.txt:

       cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.20)
       project(MyProject VERSION 1.0 LANGUAGES CXX)

       # Add klogger as subdirectory
       add_subdirectory(external/klogger)

       add_executable(my_app src/main.cpp)
       target_link_libraries(my_app PRIVATE klogger::klogger)
       target_include_directories(my_app PRIVATE external/klogger/include)

2. Using `find_package` (GitHub or installed system-wide):

    include(FetchContent)
    FetchContent_Declare(
        klogger
        GIT_REPOSITORY https://github.com/IdanKoblik/klogger.git
        GIT_TAG 2026-b1
    )

    FetchContent_MakeAvailable(klogger)
    add_executable(my_app src/main.cpp)
    target_link_libraries(my_app PRIVATE klogger::klogger)
